results.name: Denominators of resistance values < 1 ohm that can be obtained from a network of exactly 8 one-ohm resistors, but not from any network with fewer than 8 one-ohm resistors. Numerators are in A338580.
link: Hugo Pfoertner, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..156
example: The list of the 312 = A338197(8) resistance values, sorted by increasing size of R = A338580(n)/a(n) = A338608(n)/A338600(8), is the union of [1/8, 2/13, 3/17, ..., 27/28, 30/31, 34/35] and of the corresponding reciprocal resistances > 1 ohm [35/34, 31/30, 28/27, ..., 17/3, 13/2, 8].
results.author: _Hugo Pfoertner_, Nov 06 2020
